'''Ndut''' (''Ndoute'') is a [[Cangin language]] of [[Senegal]]. ''Ethnologue'' reports that it is 84% cognate (and 55% intelligible) with [[Palor language|Palor]], essentially a divergent dialect, and 68% cognate with the other Cangin languages.

